HEADWORD: Inexcusably
<hw>In`ex*cus"a*bly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>With a degree of guilt or
folly beyond excuse or justification.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Inexcusably</qex> obstinate and perverse.</q>
<rj><qau>Jortin.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
